rham, Suffolk, Anglie","Boston, Lincolnshire, England":"Boston, Lincolnshire, Anglie"},"da":{"1432–between 1465 and November 1468":"1432–fra 1465 til november 1468","1428–1465":"1428–1465","1432–1468":"1432–1468","1427–1483":"1427–1483","1463–1539":"1463–1539","1385–1440":"1385–1440","1407–1439":"1407–1439","1440":"1440","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","1426":"1426","before 20 July 1461":"før 20. juli 1461","1468":"1468","Bef 1 July 1439":"før 1. juli 1439","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1465":"1465","1463":"1463","between 1465 and November 1468":"fra 1465 til november 1468","about 1440":"omkring 1440","1407":"1407","1539":"1539","1439":"1439","1428":"1428","1427":"1427","Yorkshire, England":"Jórvík, England","Parham, Sussex, England":"Parham, Sussex, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England","Boston, Lincolnshire, England":"Boston, Lincolnshire, England"},"nl":{"1432–between 1465 and November 1468":"1432–van 1465 to november 1468","1428–1465":"1428–1465","1432–1468":"1432–1468","1427–1483":"1427–1483","1463–1539":"1463–1539","1385–1440":"1385–1440","1407–1439":"1407–1439","1440":"1440","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","1426":"1426","before 20 July 1461":"vóór 20 juli 1461","1468":"1468","Bef 1 July 1439":"vóór 1 juli 1439","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1465":"1465","1463":"1463","between 1465 and November 1468":"van 1465 to november 1468","about 1440":"circa 1440","1407":"1407","1539":"1539","1439":"1439","1428":"1428","1427":"1427","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Parham, Sussex, England":"Parham, Sussex, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England","Boston, Lincolnshire, England":"Boston, Lincolnshire, England"},"en":{"1432–between 1465 and November 1468":"1432–from 1465 to November 1468","1428–1465":"1428–1465","1432–1468":"1432–1468","1427–1483":"1427–1483","1463–1539":"1463–1539","1385–1440":"1385–1440","1407–1439":"1407–1439","1440":"1440","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","1426":"1426","before 20 July 1461":"before 20 July 1461","1468":"1468","Bef 1 July 1439":"before 1 July 1439","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1465":"1465","1463":"1463","between 1465 and November 1468":"from 1465 to November 1468","about 1440":"about 1440","1407":"1407","1539":"1539","1439":"1439","1428":"1428","1427":"1427","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Parham, Sussex, England":"Parham, Sussex, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England","Boston, Lincolnshire, England":"Boston, Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Willoughby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Willoughby, for example in Leicestershire, Lincolnshire, Nottinghamshire, and Warwickshire. They are named from an Old English +<i>wilig</i> ‘willow’ + Old Norse <i>bȳ</i> ‘farmstead, village’."],"variants":[{"name":"Wilby","meanings":["habitational name from any of the places called Wilby, in Suffolk, Norfolk, and Northamptonshire. The first placename is probably named from an Old English <i>wilig</i> ‘willow’ + Old English <i>bēag</i> ‘circle, ring’; the Norfolk placename derives from Old English <i>wilig</i> + <i>bēag</i> or Old Norse <i>bý</i> ‘farmstead, village’; the Northamptonshire placename derives from the Old Norse personal name <i>Vili</i> + <i>bý</i>.","Redmonds has demonstrated that in the parish of Hipperholme, and subsequently elsewhere in Yorkshire, <i>Wilby</i> occurs as a variant of   Willoughby  .","English:"]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":23,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Willoughby was born in 1432, in Boston, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Sir Thomas Willoughby, was 48 and his mother, Joan Arundel, was 25. He married Joan Strangways before 20 July 1461. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died from 1465 to November 1468, in his hometown."},"et":{"1432–between 1465 and November 1468":"1432–1465 kuni november 1468","1428–1465":"1428–1465","1432–1468":"1432–1468","1427–1483":"1427–1483","1463–1539":"1463–1539","1385–1440":"1385–1440","1407–1439":"1407–1439","1440":"1440","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","1426":"1426","before 20 July 1461":"enne 20. juulit 1461","1468":"1468","Bef 1 July 1439":"enne 1. juulit 1439","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1465":"1465","1463":"1463","between 1465 and November 1468":"1465 kuni november 1468","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1407":"1407","1539":"1539","1439":"1439","1428":"1428","1427":"1427","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Parham, Sussex, England":"Parham, Sussex, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England","Boston, Lincolnshire, England":"Boston, Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1432–between 1465 and